{{ 'ciem-care-system.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HowTo",
  "name": "How to Care for Custom In-Ear Monitors",
  "description": "A practical care routine for cleaning, drying, storing, and maintaining custom in-ear monitors.",
  "step": [
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Brush exterior dust away",
      "text": "Use a soft brush to clear loose dust from the shell, faceplate edges, and nozzle exterior."
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Clean the sound bores",
      "text": "Use the included cleaning tool to gently remove earwax or dust from the sound bores. Be careful not to push debris deeper."
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Care for the cable and connector",
      "text": "Disconnect by holding the connector housing, brush away lint, and avoid pulling directly on the cable."
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Protect from moisture",
      "text": "Let monitors air dry before storage and keep a fresh desiccant pack in the case."
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Store after each session",
      "text": "Return both monitors and cable to the protective case once clean and dry."
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "name": "Send blocked mesh or cracked shells for service",
      "text": "For universal monitors with mesh-equipped nozzles, bring the monitor to AAW or an authorized dealer if earwax clogs the mesh. If UIEM or CIEM shells are cracked, bring them to AAW for repair or reshell assessment."
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<div class="ciem-care">
  <section class="ciem-care-hero" aria-labelledby="ciem-care-title">
    <div class="ciem-care-wrap ciem-care-hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="ciem-care-kicker">AAW CIEM care system</p>
        <h1 id="ciem-care-title">How to Service Your IEM</h1>
        <p class="ciem-care-dek">Custom in-ear monitors live close to skin, sweat, dust, and daily handling. A short care routine keeps the shells comfortable, the sound bores open, and the cable connection dependable.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="ciem-care-quick" aria-label="Quick care checklist">
        <h2>After every session</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Brush or wipe loose debris from the shell.</li>
          <li>Check the sound bores before wax hardens.</li>
          <li>Let moisture evaporate before closing the case.</li>
          <li>Store the monitors and cable without tight bends.</li>
        </ol>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ciem-care-system" aria-labelledby="ciem-care-system-title">
    <div class="ciem-care-wrap">
      <div class="ciem-care-system-head">
        <div>
          <p class="ciem-care-kicker">The routine</p>
          <h2 id="ciem-care-system-title">Six small habits that protect fit and sound</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Work gently, always clean outward, and avoid forcing tools into openings. If debris is packed deep inside a sound bore, stop and contact AAW support rather than pushing further.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ciem-care-step-list">
        <article class="ciem-care-step">
          <figure class="ciem-care-step-media">
            <img src="{{ 'ciem-care-05-brush.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Illustration of dust being brushed from a custom in-ear monitor shell" width="1183" height="1137" loading="eager">
          </figure>
          <div class="ciem-care-step-content">
            <span class="ciem-care-step-number">Step 01</span>
            <h3>Brush loose dust away</h3>
            <p>Use a soft brush to clear lint, dry skin, and surface dust from the shell, faceplate edge, and nozzle exterior. Keep the motion light so particles lift away instead of being pressed into seams.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Brush outward from openings and edges.</li>
              <li>Avoid alcohol, solvents, and rough fabric on polished shells.</li>
              <li>Do this before deeper bore cleaning.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ciem-care-step">
          <figure class="ciem-care-step-media">
            <img src="{{ 'ciem-care-02-clean-bores.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Illustration of a cleaning tool removing debris from custom in-ear monitor sound bores" width="591" height="568" loading="lazy">
          </figure>
          <div class="ciem-care-step-content">
            <span class="ciem-care-step-number">Step 02</span>
            <h3>Clear the sound bores</h3>
            <p>Use the included cleaning tool to gently remove earwax or dust from the sound bores. Be careful not to push debris deeper.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Hold the bore downward when possible.</li>
              <li>Scoop from the opening; do not dig into the tube.</li>
              <li>Stop if the wax is hardened or lodged deep inside.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ciem-care-step">
          <figure class="ciem-care-step-media">
            <img src="{{ 'ciem-care-03-cable.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Illustration of cable connector pins being cleaned before reconnecting" width="1183" height="1137" loading="lazy">
          </figure>
          <div class="ciem-care-step-content">
            <span class="ciem-care-step-number">Step 03</span>
            <h3>Care for cable contacts</h3>
            <p>Disconnect by holding the connector housing, then inspect the pins and socket area for lint or residue. Clean dry debris with a soft brush before reconnecting.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Never pull the cable itself to disconnect.</li>
              <li>Reconnect straight, without twisting the pins.</li>
              <li>Do not use liquid cleaner on exposed contacts.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ciem-care-step">
          <figure class="ciem-care-step-media">
            <img src="{{ 'ciem-care-04-moisture.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Illustration of custom in-ear monitors stored in a protective case with a desiccant pack" width="591" height="568" loading="lazy">
          </figure>
          <div class="ciem-care-step-content">
            <span class="ciem-care-step-number">Step 04</span>
            <h3>Control moisture</h3>
            <p>After use, let the monitors air dry on a clean surface before sealing them in the case. Add a desiccant pack to help absorb moisture from sweat, humidity, or stage use.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Replace desiccant packs when saturated or expired.</li>
              <li>Keep monitors away from heat, dryers, and direct sun.</li>
              <li>If exposed to water, disconnect the cable and let everything dry fully.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ciem-care-step">
          <figure class="ciem-care-step-media">
            <img src="{{ 'ciem-care-01-store.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Illustration of custom in-ear monitors being placed into a protective storage case" width="591" height="568" loading="lazy">
          </figure>
          <div class="ciem-care-step-content">
            <span class="ciem-care-step-number">Step 05</span>
            <h3>Store without stress</h3>
            <p>Return the monitors to their protective case once they are clean and dry. Coil the cable loosely so the connectors and memory wire are not under tension.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Use the case whenever the monitors are not in your ears.</li>
              <li>Keep loose tools, keys, and metal objects away from the shells.</li>
              <li>Do not store monitors in pockets or bags without protection.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ciem-care-step">
          <figure class="ciem-care-step-media">
            <img src="{{ 'ciem-care-06-service.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Illustration of mesh replacement and cracked shell repair for in-ear monitors" width="574" height="564" loading="lazy">
          </figure>
          <div class="ciem-care-step-content">
            <span class="ciem-care-step-number">Step 06</span>
            <h3>Send blocked mesh or cracked shells for service</h3>
            <p>For universal monitors with mesh-equipped nozzles, bring the monitor to AAW or an authorized dealer if earwax clogs the mesh. If UIEM or CIEM shells are cracked, bring them to AAW for repair or reshell assessment.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Do not pick, pierce, or push through a clogged mesh.</li>
              <li>Use AAW or an authorized dealer for mesh replacement.</li>
              <li>Stop using cracked shells until they are assessed for repair or reshell.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ciem-care-maintenance" aria-labelledby="ciem-care-rhythm-title">
    <div class="ciem-care-wrap ciem-care-maintenance-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="ciem-care-kicker">Service rhythm</p>
        <h2 id="ciem-care-rhythm-title">When to clean, dry, and ask for help</h2>
        <p>A little care after each session prevents most problems. Professional service is for blocked bores, loose parts, visible cracks, intermittent channels, or anything that feels forced.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ciem-care-rhythm">
        <article>
          <h3>Every use</h3>
          <p>Wipe or brush the shells, check the bore openings, and let moisture dry before storage.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Weekly</h3>
          <p>Inspect cable contacts, case padding, desiccant condition, and the shell surface under good light.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Send for service</h3>
          <p>Contact AAW if the bore is blocked deep inside, the fit changes suddenly, the shell is damaged, or one side becomes intermittent.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ciem-care-support" aria-labelledby="ciem-care-support-title">
    <div class="ciem-care-wrap ciem-care-support-grid">
      <div>
        <h2 id="ciem-care-support-title">Need a deeper service?</h2>
        <p>For blocked sound tubes, damaged shells, cable faults, or refit questions, get in touch with AAW before attempting aggressive cleaning at home.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ciem-care-actions">
        <a class="ciem-care-btn" href="/pages/contact">Contact AAW</a>
        <a class="ciem-care-btn secondary" href="/pages/store-locator">Find a dealer</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

